The data lost after file saving at the moment only observed in Android emulator.
The reason is that the output stream is only closed after writing without flush, and the emulator needs more time to flush it automaically.
Solution: before stream close flush and also sync the file descriptor:
```
            // Explicitly flush the stream to force buffered output to be written
            stream.flush();
            // For ContentResolver streams, also sync the file descriptor to
            // ensure the data is physically written to storage.
            if (stream instanceof FileOutputStream)
            {
                ((FileOutputStream) stream).getFD().sync();
            }
            stream.close();
```

